A reddish-orange cylindrical block (likely index 11) sits on top of the triangle-rectangle stack.  A slightly curved, reddish-orange block (likely index 1) sits above that, creating the final structure of the first set.

   **Structure 2 (Right):** Composed of 4 blocks. It appears to have 2 layers. The spatial relationships are: A yellow rectangular block (likely index 9) forms the base. A red, square block (likely index 2) is placed on the yellow one, vertically stacked in the middle.  Next to it, and above the yellow block, are two vertically stacked blocks: green (likely index 7) and blue (likely index 4).
